On Feb 28, 2008, at 12:07 PM, C. Dreike, Advantage Automation, Inc  
wrote:

> Will hydraulic lifters make a significant difference?

Much quieter than solids especially without the camper mattress  
muffling the engine. The Hydraulic engines almost don't sound like VWs.

> What are the ups and downs of using them?

You have to give them a regular maintenance through oil changes. If  
they bleed down you may have to remove them.

Valve adjustments are done quicker. See my webpage for details:

http://www.ratwell.com/technical/HydraulicLifters.html

